Setting up Python
=================
- We are using Python 2.7
https://www.python.org/download
(pretty handy: http://inventwithpython.com/pygame/chapter1.html)
- You also need the following Python libraries:
-- pygame
http://pygame.org/download.shtml
-- (curses, for keyboard input & time for the timing aspect in Python - look on the web how to install these)

- Your sound files need to be in the same folder as your python script.


Setting up your Makey Makey
==============================
Connect the diamond shape of your knitted Pattern-keyboard to the ground of your MakeyMakey
Connect the square shapes of your knitted Pattern-keyboard to the letters a & d of your MakeyMakey

Launch the script
=================
- Depending on your operating system, you need to launch the following python script with python - we do this via our Linux terminal
$python Pattern-keyboard.py
- Press the letter q to quit this Python script
